<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id13a5b1b7-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s149"><num value="149">§ 149.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When used in this subchapter—</chapeau><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id13a5b1b8-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s149/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> The term “person” means an individual, partnership, association, or corporation.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id13a5b1b9-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s149/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> The term “United States” means the fifty States and the District of Columbia.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id13a5b1ba-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-02-15/ch155/s9">Feb. 15, 1927, ch. 155, § 9</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1103">44 Stat. 1103</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/86/70/s19">Pub. L. 86–70, § 19</ref>, <date date="1959-06-25">June 25, 1959</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/73/145">73 Stat. 145</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/86/624/s15">Pub. L. 86–624, § 15</ref>, <date date="1960-07-12">July 12, 1960</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/74/415">74 Stat. 415</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id13a5b1bb-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id13a5b1bc-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id13a5b1bd-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1960—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/86/624">Pub. L. 86–624</ref> substituted “means the fifty States and the District of Columbia” for “means continental United States, including Alaska”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1959—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/86/70">Pub. L. 86–70</ref> inserted “, including Alaska” after “continental United States”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
